parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SBC system can cause a sudden loss of brake power, leading to increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: red warning light on the dashboard
feeling of no brakes or reduced braking power
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system leak or vapor issue can cause a strong smell of gasoline in the garage or passenger compartment, potentially leading to a fire hazard or explosion.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline or fuel vapors in the garage or passenger compartment

especially when the fuel tank is full; smell subsides when fuel tank level reaches 3/4 to 1/2 full; smell detectable near the left rear of the vehicle; smell coming from underneath the rear passenger seat; vehicle takes longer to start
turning over several times before starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank and Fuel Filter Module Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of fuel from the fuel tank and fuel filter modules can cause a strong gasoline odor, which can lead to health risks, fire hazards, and environmental pollution. If left unchecked, it can also cause fuel to accumulate under the vehicle, posing a significant safety risk.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odor inside and outside the vehicle
fuel smell coming from under the back seat
fuel fumes noticed inside the house
puddle of gas under the back seat.
